The paper discusses the training of adversarial neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the proposed modification to stochastic gradient descent has implications for control systems (cs.SY), as it enables stable training with a wider range of parameters.
